org.apache.poi.util

Class IntList

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.poi.util.IntList

  • public class IntList
extends java.lang.Object
    A List of int's; as full an implementation of the java.util.List interface as possible, with an eye toward minimal creation of objects the mimicry of List is as follows:
    • if possible, operations designated 'optional' in the List interface are attempted
    • wherever the List interface refers to an Object, substitute int
    • wherever the List interface refers to a Collection or List, substitute IntList
    the mimicry is not perfect, however:
    • operations involving Iterators or ListIterators are not supported
    • remove(Object) becomes removeValue to distinguish it from remove(int index)
    • subList is not supported
    (int的列表;尽可能完整地实现java.util.List接口，着眼于最少地创建对象，List的模仿如下：如果可能，只要List接口引用对象，就会尝试在List接口中指定为“可选”的操作，在List接口引用Collection或List的地方替换int，替换IntList，模仿并不完美，但是：不支持涉及Iterators或ListIterators的操作remove（对象）变成removeValue以将其与remove（int index）区分开来不支持子列表)
    Author:
    Marc Johnson

      • addAll

        public boolean addAll(int index,
                      IntList c)
        Inserts all of the elements in the specified collection into this list at the specified position. Shifts the element currently at that position (if any) and any subsequent elements to the right (increases their indices). The new elements will appear in this list in the order that they are returned by the specified collection's iterator. The behavior of this operation is unspecified if the specified collection is modified while the operation is in progress. (Note that this will occur if the specified collection is this list, and it's nonempty.)(将指定集合中的所有元素初始化到此列表的指定位置。将当前位于该位置的元素（如果有的话）和任何后续元素向右移动（增加其索引）。新元素将按照指定集合迭代器返回的顺序出现在此列表中。如果在操作进行时修改了指定的集合，则未指定此操作的行为。(Note如果指定的集合是此列表并且非空，就会发生这种情况。）)
        Parameters:
        index - index at which to insert first element from the specified collection.(index -要插入指定集合中的第一个元素的索引。)
        c - elements to be inserted into this list.(c -要插入此列表的元素。)
        Returns:
        true if this list changed as a result of the call.(如果此列表因呼叫而更改，则为真。)

        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index is out of range (index < 0 || index > size())(java.lang. IndexOutOfBoundsResponse-如果索引超出范围（index < 0|| index > size（））)

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Compares the specified object with this list for equality. Returns true if and only if the specified object is also a list, both lists have the same size, and all corresponding pairs of elements in the two lists are equal. (Two elements e1 and e2 are equal if e1 == e2.) In other words, two lists are defined to be equal if they contain the same elements in the same order. This definition ensures that the equals method works properly across different implementations of the List interface.(将指定对象与此列表进行相等性比较。当且仅当指定的对象也是列表、两个列表具有相同的大小并且两个列表中所有对应的元素对相等时，才会返回true。(Two如果e1 == e2，元素e1和e2相等。）换句话说，如果两个列表包含相同顺序的相同元素，则它们被定义为相等。此定义确保equals方法在List接口的不同实现中正常工作。)
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        o - the object to be compared for equality with this list.(o -要比较与此列表是否相等的对象。)
        Returns:
        true if the specified object is equal to this list.(如果指定的对象等于此列表，则为真。)

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Returns the hash code value for this list. The hash code of a list is defined to be the result of the following calculation: hashCode = 1; Iterator i = list.iterator(); while (i.hasNext()) { Object obj = i.next(); hashCode = 31*hashCode + (obj==null ? 0 : obj.hashCode()); } This ensures that list1.equals(list2) implies that list1.hashCode()==list2.hashCode() for any two lists, list1 and list2, as required by the general contract of Object.hashCode.(返回此列表的哈希码值。列表的哈希码被定义为以下计算的结果：hashCode = 1; Iterator i = list.iterator（）; while（i.hasNext（）{对象obj = i.next（）; hashCode = 31*hashCode +（obj==空？0：obj.hashCode（））;}这确保了list1.equals（list 2）意味着对于任何两个列表，list 1和list 2，list1.hashCode（）==list2.hashCode（），正如Object. hashCode的一般约定所要求的那样。)
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        the hash code value for this list.(此列表的哈希码值。)
